FBIS4-35958 "drnes108_j_94055" FBIS-NES-94-108 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen `National Assembly' Meets, Appoints Officers `National Assembly' Meets, Appoints Officers EA0606140694 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 0330 GMT 6 Jun 94 EA0606140694 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 0330 GMT 6 Jun 94 Arabic BFN [Text] The National Assembly Presidium held a [word indistinct] meeting this morning under the chairmanship of Speaker Anis Hasan Yahya. During this meeting, the assembly discussed a number of topics on its agenda and made the necessary decisions. The presidium endorsed the distribution of duties among its members as follows: (?Sha'fil 'Umar Ali), deputy assembly speaker for parliamentary affairs and foreign liaison; Ahmad Ubayd Bin Daghr, deputy assembly speaker for organizational and technical affairs; 'Abd-al-Qawi Muhammad Rashad, deputy assembly speaker for permanent committees' affairs; 'Abd-al-Rahman Asim, deputy assembly speaker for the affairs of the government apparatus and the public and mixed sectors. The presidium also endorsed the appointment of Brother Taha 'Abdallah Muhammad as secretary general of the National Assembly Presidium.
